function y = somb(x)%SOMB(X) is the ratio 2J1(pi.x)/(pi.x) of the elements of X.% Def of somb(x) is by Gaskill (1978), p. 72.% somb(x) crosses zero at x=1.22%%%LNT. 2-NOV-94%LNT 23Jun05. Last line needs to be real(y) rather than abs(y) to show the%   zero-crossing nature of somb.%% © 1994 Larry Thibos, Indiana University% 2013.  At some unknown date, Matlab changed the name of bessel to besseljxx = x;                   % a local copy i = find(xx == 0);        % detect zero valuesif any(i)   xx(i) = eps;		         % replace zeros with smallest number   endy = 2*besselj(1,pi*xx)./(pi*xx);   % avoids divide-by-zero errorsy = real(y);						% ignore small imaginary components